@levis and @beams_official are skipping years of wear and going straight to the good part. Their new 501 Loose jeans recreate the look of denim worn nearly to death, with frayed rips and chaotic zig-zag stitching that feels more hand-repaired than factory-finished.⁠
⁠
The release arrives as patched, dirtied, and faux-repaired denim appears across Ralph Lauren, JW Anderson, and Prada. Vintage heads already know the rule: denim gets better when damaged.

